{{Quote|Cut cut cut! And George said: 'Brian, you goddamn mad bastard. That's exactly what I wanted!'|Brian Blessed recalls the shooting of ''The Phantom Menace'', where he gave a performance of Boss Nass that was met with approval from director George Lucas|<ref name="Blessed" />}}
'''Brian Blessed''' is an [[Wikipedia:England|English]] actor who portrayed [[Boss]] [[Rugor Nass]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]. He also appeared as [[Wikipedia:Prince Vultan|Prince Vultan]] in the [[1980]] cult film [[Wikipedia:Flash Gordon (film)|''Flash Gordon'']].

Blessed rose to fame for portraying PC "Fancy" Smith in the long running BBC police drama Z-Cars. He portrayed [[Wikipedia:Roman Emperor|Roman Emperor]] [[Wikipedia:Augustus|Augustus]] in the 1976 television series [[Wikipedia:I, Claudius (TV series)|''I, Claudius'']]. Blessed appeared in the 1988 miniseries [[Wikipedia:War and Remembrance|''War and Remembrance'']], in which [[Kenneth Colley]] also appeared. He is also known for playing King Yrcanos in the ''[[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|Doctor Who]]'' story [[Wikipedia:Mindwarp|Mindwarp]] (having once been offered the role of the Second Doctor) and having a recurring role in the first series of [[Wikipedia:The Black Adder|''Blackadder'']] as the fictional [[Wikipedia:King Richard IV|King Richard IV]].

Blessed is known for a booming voice and a loud personality that has made him a popular choice in animation, both on television in programs such as [[Wikipedia:Peppa Pig|''Peppa Pig'']] and [[Wikipedia:The Amazing World of Gumball|''The Amazing World of Gumball'']], as well as films such as [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney's]] [[Wikipedia:Tarzan (1999 film)|''Tarzan'']].

==Biography==
During a conversation with Blessed, director [[George Lucas]] stated that the actor's energy was needed for ''The Phantom Menace'', and that he himself thought of casting Blessed as one of the [[Jedi]] but he was "much too powerful" for the part.<ref name="Blessed">{{YouTube|video=wTJ3DSNP6Dg|text=Boss Nass Warned George Lucas about Jar Jar Binks (Brian Blessed Interview)|channel=channel/UCKhZplFZ1QaLqA_fCTVlU_g|name=The Geeknd <nowiki>[Jamie Stangroom]</nowiki>|archivedate=20201103070721}}</ref>

